# Normalize all text files to LF line endings in the repository.
# This overrides core.autocrlf=true (common on Windows/Scoop Git installs),
# which causes spurious "dirty" working-tree states because git's stat-cache
# sees a line-ending filter mismatch even when file content is byte-identical.
#
# With this file in place:
#   - On checkout, files keep LF (no CRLF conversion)
#   - On commit, CRLF is normalized to LF
#   - git diff-index sees no phantom changes
#   - build-aux/git-version.sh no longer appends -dirty

* text=auto eol=lf
